## Design: Custom Subdomain add-on (+ Own Domain purchase option)

### What the codebase gives me (so I mirror it, not reinvent)
There's an **exact precedent**: the `oauth` "$10 add-on" (`security` category). It's config-driven pricing → entitlement in `organizations.metadata.subscription.products` → gated `isProductUnlocked(getOrgEntitlements(org), 'oauth')` → a conditionally-rendered **OAuth tab** in the org-settings dialog, backed by a dedicated table + server actions. I'll follow this pattern beat-for-beat. Orgs are `uuid`-keyed in the live DB (Prisma is vestigial), schema is applied via `npm run db:push`, and Supabase-js is the real data layer.

### 1. Pricing (`lib/pricing/plans.js`) — both options, no new Stripe code
- Two new products: `{ id: "subdomain", …, category: "subdomain" }` and `{ id: "custom_domain", …, category: "domain" }`.
- Two new `productCategories`: `subdomain` (**rate 5**) and `domain` (**rate 10**) — separate categories because the prices differ and the calculator prices per-category.
- Add `subdomain: 0, domain: 0` to every plan's `productAllowances` (so they're never free / never `NaN`). `betaPlan` has no allowances object — unaffected, matching the oauth note.
- Add icons to `PRODUCT_ICONS` in `plan_cards.jsx` (`Globe` / `Link`). The calculator renders new categories automatically. Billed as a delta through existing Stripe checkout.

### 2. Storage — a real `subdomain` column (needs a global uniqueness check → promote, don't bag it)
- New idempotent DDL: `alter table public.organizations add column if not exists subdomain text;` + a **unique index** on `lower(subdomain)` where not null. Applied via `db:push`.
- I'll add `subdomain` to `ORG_SELECT_FIELDS` so it flows through `getUserOrganizations`.

### 3. Settings — a new "Domain" tab (gated), only the subdomain part functional
- Gate exactly like oauth: `hasDomainAddon = isProductUnlocked(getOrgEntitlements(org), 'subdomain')`; conditionally add `{ id: 'domain', label: 'Domain' }` to the tab array.
- New `DomainTab` component: subdomain input, **live preview** (`yourname.geiger.studio` updates as you type), inline validation (3–63 chars, `[a-z0-9-]`, no leading/trailing hyphen, reserved-word blocklist), **debounced availability check** (green "available" / red "taken"), a **Claim** button, and once claimed a copyable live link + "Release" action.
- Because `custom_domain` is purchased but **not built yet**, the tab shows a functional Subdomain section and a **"Custom domain — coming soon"** placeholder section (only if that product is owned).

### 4. Data layer + server actions (mirror `oauth-actions.js`)
- `app/org/subdomain-actions.js` (`"use server"`): `checkSubdomainAvailableAction(sub)`, `setOrgSubdomainAction(orgId, sub)`, `clearOrgSubdomainAction(orgId)`. Each verifies **ownership** via the user's RLS client **and** re-derives entitlement (`isProductUnlocked`) server-side, then does the global-uniqueness check + write via the **service-role admin client** (RLS hides other orgs from anon) — same split the oauth actions use. Returns `{ ok, … }`; the client owns toasts.

### 5. Wildcard subdomain routing — the tenant view
- **Session across subdomains:** set `NEXT_PUBLIC_COOKIE_DOMAIN=.geiger.studio` (already wired into all three Supabase clients) so the auth session works on `*.geiger.studio`.
- **Filtering the org list:** in `app/org/page.js` (server component), read the host via `headers()`, extract the subdomain, and if it's a real org subdomain, **show only that org** and skip the empty→`/onboarding` redirect. Everything else is untouched — all product routes are path-based and host-agnostic, so "everything is the same" holds. A tiny pure helper `lib/tenant/subdomain.js` (`extractSubdomain(host)`, ignoring `www`, `localhost`, bare apex, and `*.vercel.app` preview hosts) keeps this testable.

